rtment is to provide quality professional police services to the community of VMI  to enforce laws and Post policies  to serve and protect the Corp of Cadets  faculty and staff  alumni and visitors  to prevent and detect criminal activity  and to reduce the fear of crime through community partnerships  About The VMI Police Department VMI has a fully trained and certified Police Department which provides for the safety and security of the Institute 24 hours a day  VMI Police Department is staffed by ten full time  two part time certified police officers and six part time security officers  VMI Police officers are responsible for crime prevention  traffic enforcement and the investigation and prosecution of all criminal offenses that occur on Post  at any of VMI s outlying properties and on the streets and sidewalks adjoining Post  All VMI Police officers are graduates of regional criminal justice training academies and are fully certified by the Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services  Most VMI officers have many years of experience working for municipal police or sheriff s departments prior to being employed by VMI  Each officer is required to complete 40 hours of in service training biennially and to pass an annual firearms qualification  In addition  VMI officers have additional specialty training in bicycle patrol  tactical operations  crisis negotiations  crime prevention  dignitary protection  sexual assault and intimate partner violence investigation  and more  Several officers are certified as criminal justice instructors and regularly teach at local criminal justice academies  Officers conduct training for cadets and employees on topics relating to crime prevention and personal safety  as well as conducting programs in the community and local elementary schools  VMI Police Department has a full time detective  responsible for investigating any serious offenses that occur on VMI Property  following up on initial reports taken by the patrol officers and processing crime scenes and evidence  The Department also has a fully trained Special Emergency Response Team  capable of responding to significant threats to the safety of the VMI community and certified Crisis Negotiators  VMI Police Department works closely with the Commandant s staff and student governing bodies to enforce VMI rules and regulations  VMI Police also work closely with Lexington Police Department  Rockbridge County Sheriff s Department and Virginia State Police on incidents occurring off Post that involve cadets  Policies Alcohol and Drug Policy Sexual Assault Policy Lost and Found Motor Vehicle Policy Driver Qualification and Vehicle Use Policy Appeals to Parking Violation VMI Administration VMI Police Crime Prevention Safety Tips Policies Clery Act Info Threat Assessment Team Fire Safety Report Law Enforcement Links Silent Witness Property ID Database Parking Emergency  911 or 9 911 Report a Crime Anonymously Dispatch   540  463 9177 Office   540  464 7017 Email  VMI Police VMI Police 301 Letcher Avenue 200 Level BOQ Lexington  VA  24450  VMI Administration VMI Police Crime Prevention Safety Tips Policies Clery Act Info Threat Assessment Team Fire Safety Report Law Enforcement Links Silent Witness Property ID Database Parking Emergency  911 or 9 911 Report a Crime Anonymously Dispatch   540  463 9177 Office   540  464 7017 Email  VMI Police VMI Police 301 Letcher Avenue 200 Level BOQ Lexington  VA  24450 VMI Administration VMI Police Crime Prevention Safety Tips Policies Clery Act Info Threat Assessment Team Fire Safety Report Law Enforcement Links Silent Witness Property ID Database Parking VMI Administration VMI Administration VMI Police VMI Police VMI Police Crime Prevention Crime Prevention Safety Tips Safety Tips Policies Policies Clery Act Info Clery Act Info Threat Assessment Team Threat Assessment Team Fire Safety Report Fire Safety Report Law Enforcement Links Law Enforcement Links Silent Witness Silent Witness Property ID Database Property ID Database Parking Parking Emergency  911 or 9 911 Report a Crime Anonymously Dispatch   540  463 9177 Office   540  464 7017 Email  VMI Police VMI Police 301 Letcher Avenue 200 Level BOQ Lexington  VA  24450 Emergency  911 or 9 911 Report a Crime Anonymously Dispatch   540  463 9177 Office   540  464 7017 Email  VMI Police VMI Police 301 Letcher Avenue 200 Level BOQ Lexington  VA  24450 Emergency  911 or 9 911    Report a Crime Anonymously Report a Crime Anonymously     Email  VMI Police      VMI Police Department Download Annual Security Report Vision We are committed to working with all parts of the community to maintain the benevolent quality of life at the Virginia Military Institute and in the larger Lexington area by forming community partnerships and actively seeking input and participation in crime prevention and reduction programs  We see the police function as a broad mandate to participate in programs to improve the community  Mission Statement The mission of the Virginia Military Institute Police Department is to provide quality professional police services to the community of VMI  to enforce laws and Post policies  to serve and protect the Corp of Cadets  faculty and staff  alumni and visitors  to prevent and detect criminal activity  and to reduce the fear of crime through community partnerships  About The VMI Police Department VMI has a fully trained and certified Police Department which provides for the safety and security of the Institute 24 hours a day  VMI Police Department is staffed by ten full time  two part time certified police officers and six part time security officers  VMI Police officers are responsible for crime prevention  traffic enforcement and the investigation and prosecution of all criminal offenses that occur on Post  at any of VMI s outlying properties and on the streets and sidewalks adjoining Post  All VMI Police officers are graduates of regional criminal justice training academies and are fully certified by the Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services  Most VMI officers have many years of experience working for municipal police or sheriff s departments prior to being employed by VMI  Each officer is required to complete 40 hours of in service training biennially and to pass an annual firearms qualification  In addition  VMI officers have additional specialty training in bicycle patrol  tactical operations  crisis negotiations  crime prevention  dignitary protection  sexual assault and intimate partner violence investigation  and more  Several officers are certified as criminal justice instructors and regularly teach at local criminal justice academies  Officers conduct training for cadets and employees on topics relating to crime prevention and personal safety  as well as conducting programs in the community and local elementary schools  VMI Police Department has a full time detective  responsible for investigating any serious offenses that occur on VMI Property  following up on initial reports taken by the patrol officers and processing crime scenes and evidence  The Department also has a fully trained Special Emergency Response Team  capable of responding to significant threats to the safety of the VMI community and certified Crisis Negotiators  VMI Police Department works closely with the Commandant s staff and student governing bodies to enforce VMI rules and regulations  VMI Police also work closely with Lexington Police Department  Rockbridge County Sheriff s Department and Virginia State Police on incidents occurring off Post that involve cadets  Policies Alcohol and Drug Policy Sexual Assault Policy Lost and Found Motor Vehicle Policy Driver Qualification and Vehicle Use Policy Appeals to Parking Violation      VMI Police Department Download Annual Security Report Vision We are committed to working with all parts of the community to maintain the benevolent quality of life at the Virginia Military Institute and in the larger Lexington area by forming community partnerships and actively seeking input and participation in crime prevention and reduction programs  We see the police function as a broad mandate to participate in programs to improve the community  Mission Statement The mission of the Virginia Military Institute Police Department is to provide quality professional police services to the community of VMI  to enforce laws and Post policies  to serve and protect the Corp of Cadets  faculty and staff  alumni and visitors  to prevent and detect criminal activity  and to reduce the fear of crime through community partnerships  About The VMI Police Department VMI has a fully trained and certified Police Department which provides for the safety and security of the Institute 24 hours a day  VMI Police Department is staffed by ten full time  two part time certified police officers and six part time security officers  VMI Police officers are responsible for crime prevention  traffic enforcement and the investigation and prosecution of all criminal offenses that occur on Post  at any of VMI s outlying properties and on the streets and sidewalks adjoining Post  All VMI Police officers are graduates of regional criminal justice training academies and are fully certified by the Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services  Most VMI officers have many years of experience working for municipal police or sheriff s departments prior to being employed by VMI  Each officer is required to complete 40 hours of in service training biennially and to pass an annual firearms qualification  In addition  VMI officers have additional specialty training in bicycle patrol  tactical operations  crisis negotiations  crime prevention  dignitary protection  sexual assault and intimate partner violence investigation  and more  Several officers are certified as criminal justice instructors and regularly teach at local criminal justice academies  Officers conduct training for cadets and employees on topics relating to crime prevention and personal safety  as well as conducting programs in the community and local elementary schools  VMI Police Department has a full time detective  responsible for investigating any serious offenses that occur on VMI Property  following up on initial reports taken by the patrol officers and processing crime scenes and evidence  The Department also has a fully trained Special Emergency Response Team  capable of responding to significant threats to the safety of the VMI community and certified Crisis Negotiators  VMI Police Department works closely with the Commandant s staff and student governing bodies to enforce VMI rules and regulations  VMI Police also work closely with Lexington Police Department  Rockbridge County Sheriff s Department and Virginia State Police on incidents occurring off Post that involve cadets VMI Police Department Download Annual Security Report Download Annual Security Report Vision We are committed to working with all parts of the community to maintain the benevolent quality of life at the Virginia Military Institute and in the larger Lexington area by forming community partnerships and actively seeking input and participation in crime prevention and reduction programs  We see the police function as a broad mandate to participate in programs to improve the community Vision Vision  Mission Statement The mission of the Virginia Military Institute Police Department is to provide quality professional police services to the community of VMI  to enforce laws and Post policies  to serve and protect the Corp of Cadets  faculty and staff  alumni and visitors  to prevent and detect criminal activity  and to reduce the fear of crime through community partnerships Mission Statement Mission Statement  About The VMI Police Department VMI has a fully trained and certified Police Department which provides for the safety and security of the Institute 24 hours a day  VMI Police Department is staffed by ten full time  two part time certified police officers and six part time security officers  VMI Police officers are responsible for crime prevention  traffic enforcement and the investigation and prosecution of all criminal offenses that occur on Post  at any of VMI s outlying properties and on the streets and sidewalks adjoining Post About The VMI Police Department About The VMI Police Department  All VMI Police officers are graduates of regional criminal justice training academies and are fully certified by the Virginia Department of Criminal Justice Services  Most VMI officers have many years of experience working for municipal police or sheriff s departments prior to being employed by VMI  Each officer is required to complete 40 hours of in service training biennially and to pass an annual firearms qualification  In addition  VMI officers have additional specialty training in bicycle patrol  tactical operations  crisis negotiations  crime prevention  dignitary protection  sexual assault and intimate partner violence investigation  and more Several officers are certified as criminal justice instructors and regularly teach at local criminal justice academies  Officers conduct training for cadets and employees on topics relating to crime prevention and personal safety  as well as conducting programs in the community and local elementary schools VMI Police Department has a full time detective  responsible for investigating any serious offenses that occur on VMI Property  following up on initial reports taken by the patrol officers and processing crime scenes and evidence  The Department also has a fully trained Special Emergency Response Team  capable of responding to significant threats to the safety of the VMI community and certified Crisis Negotiators VMI Police Department works closely with the Commandant s staff and student governing bodies to enforce VMI rules and regulations  VMI Police also work closely with Lexington Police Department  Rockbridge County Sheriff s Department and Virginia State Police on incidents occurring of